not required to check.. directly proceed for next steps
Consider a scenario if I get zero pel logs then I will able to catch the issue even before processing PEL logs for other purpose.
can we make it two lines?
its under 110 chars . it should be fine with current one.
Verify if no PELs are present in BMC else raise an exception.
instead of pass return True.. Incase some one needs to capture the result.
Check no PEL log exists and verify PEL logs

Compare PEL log attributes like "SRC", "Created at" with Redfish event log attributes like "EventId", "Created". 
Return False if they do not match.

This keyword is to compare the given pel_inv values with event_entries. Going back and validating whether the PEL exists in BMC should not be part of the keyword. This keyword should be called only when a PEL exists and needs to be compared. The caller needs to take care of it.

"Verify PEL And Redfish Event Log Are Same" this keyword run this command pel_utils.get_pel_data_from_bmc -> peltool -l (get list of PEL data)

"Compare PEL And Redfish Event Log" this keyword will run this command peltool -I <individual pel id>


* Consider a scenario if I get zero PEL list logs or PEL individual log data then I will able to catch the issue even before processing PEL logs for other purpose.

Why are we continuing the loop here?
What is the expectation from the caller? Is it a 1-1 comparison between PEL and Redfish event log? If yes, then it is not required to continue for loop.
If not, then a comparison of the BMC ID present in PEL should be verified first to make sure we are looking at the correct Redfish event log before comparing the SRC and date time.
I have changed the code, in case if any difference in PEL attributes then return False and fail the TC.

Why is this an error scenario? 
The validation should be to check that there are no PELs and no entry in Redfish event log too. Only if they do not match then you should fail here.
Get PEL Software Inventory - I followed naming convention from code update and other places. So will continue with current keyword name.

Please move this to lib/pel_utils.py as we have all PEL related methods there. This resource file has methods with Redfish Event logs. So let us keep it that way for clarity.
Do not name this keyword as Get PEL Software Inventory. Rename it to 'Get PEL Details' in that library.
You will get the value 'PEL not found' if you try to do a peltool -i on non existing PEL. So modify you below check accordingly.
instead of line 341 and 345, you can fail if pel_length(line 340) != event_length(line 344)
I will keep them separate and compare with 0.
